column1: Significant reductions in anxiety sensitivity, fear of bodily sensations, and general psychopathology (GSI) alongside increased social support outweigh declines in positive mental health and rising dysfunctional attitudes, suggesting overall improvement.

Elevated T1 psychopathology (GSI=1.51) and worsening anxiety sensitivity, fear of bodily sensations, and dysfunctional attitudes outweigh protective factors like improved self-efficacy and reduced GSI.
